---
import BaseLayout from '../../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
import '../../styles/content.css';
---
<BaseLayout title="Medical Equipment Planning for New Hospital Construction | Estrelis.ai" description="Plan medical equipment for new hospital construction projects. AI-powered catalog management, Revit BIM sync, budget tracking, and procurement workflows from design through move-in.">

  <section class="content-hero">
    <h1>Equipment Planning for New Hospital Construction</h1>
    <p>New healthcare facilities require tens of thousands of equipment items coordinated across hundreds of rooms. Estrelis brings AI-powered automation to every phase — from initial room planning through procurement and installation.</p>
  </section>

  <section class="content-section">
    <h2>The Challenge</h2>
    <p>New hospital construction projects typically involve 10,000 to 50,000 individual equipment line items spread across operating rooms, imaging suites, patient rooms, labs, and support spaces. Traditional planning methods rely on disconnected spreadsheets, manual catalog lookups, and fragmented email chains — creating delays, errors, and budget overruns.</p>
  </section>

  <section class="content-section">
    <h2>How Estrelis Transforms New Construction Planning</h2>
    <div class="content-grid">
      <div class="content-card">
        <h3>AI-Powered Room Templates</h3>
        <p>Start with intelligent room templates that pre-populate equipment lists based on room type, acuity level, and department standards. AI suggests items based on similar rooms across your project portfolio.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="content-card">
        <h3>Revit BIM Synchronization</h3>
        <p>Sync equipment plans directly with architectural BIM models. Room and level hierarchies flow from Revit, keeping design and planning teams coordinated in real time.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="content-card">
        <h3>Real-Time Budget Visibility</h3>
        <p>Track equipment budgets across every department, building, and project phase. Variance alerts catch overruns early — before they become change orders.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="content-card">
        <h3>Procurement Coordination</h3>
        <p>Generate RFQs, compare vendor quotes, manage approvals, and create purchase orders — all from one platform. No more switching between spreadsheets and email.</p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="content-section">
    <h2>Built for Healthcare Construction Teams</h2>
    <ul>
      <li>Equipment planners managing multi-building campuses</li>
      <li>Healthcare architects coordinating with Revit models</li>
      <li>Project managers tracking budgets across departments</li>
      <li>Procurement teams managing vendor relationships and RFQs</li>
      <li>Healthcare system owners reviewing equipment plans via client portal</li>
    </ul>
  </section>

  <nav class="related">
    <h3>Related</h3>
    <div class="related-links">
      <a href="/use-cases/renovation/">Renovation Planning</a>
      <a href="/integrations/revit/">Revit Integration</a>
      <a href="/compare/spreadsheets/">vs Spreadsheets</a>
